{
  "total_duration": 454.807,
  "lines": [
    {
      "i": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 12.84,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "你刚搬到一个新地方。第二天，有人敲门，做了一件很奇怪的事。你以为这是一次偶然事件，后来邻居一句话告诉你：原来整条街早就认识他。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 1,
      "start": 13.19,
      "end": 31.71,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "先把画面摆对：这不是中国高层小区的电梯间，也不是小朋友自己开门。故事发生在英国老式街区，临街小房子的门直接靠近街道；如果今天真的有陌生人敲门，小朋友应该叫爸爸妈妈、门卫或邻居来处理。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 2,
      "start": 32.06,
      "end": 48.211,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的幽默也不是嘲笑贫穷。真正的笑点是信息差：叙述者刚搬到"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Bridge Street"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，还不懂这里的街区惯例；但大家都知道"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Percy Buttons"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，珀西·巴顿斯。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 3,
      "start": 48.561,
      "end": 62.561,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "故事一开始，叙述者说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I have just moved to a house in Bridge Street."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这句话很关键，不只是交代地址，而是在说：我刚来，我是新人，我还不知道这条街上的人和规矩。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 4,
      "start": 62.911,
      "end": 78.555,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二天，"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "a beggar knocked at my door"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。在这种老式街屋里，门口就是街道，所以这个敲门动作才合理。Percy 请求一顿饭和一杯啤酒；啤酒只是原文里的成人生活细节，不是让小朋友模仿。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 5,
      "start": 78.905,
      "end": 97.112,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "接着他给出一个奇怪的交换："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "In return for this"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，作为回报，他"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "stood on his head and sang songs"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，倒立唱歌。叙述者很惊讶，但还是给了他一顿饭。Percy 吃完、喝完，又把一块奶酪放进口袋，离开了。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 6,
      "start": 97.462,
      "end": 119.298,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "最后，邻居揭开答案："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Everybody knows him."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "他叫"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Percy Buttons"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。他"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "calls at every house in the street once a month"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，每个月拜访这条街上的每户人家，而且总是要同样的东西。叙述者以为是一次怪事，其实这是街区里大家都知道的固定节目。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 7,
      "start": 119.648,
      "end": 126.168,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这课最容易误会的地方，是把它当成一个“乞丐很滑稽”的笑话。我们不要这样读。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 8,
      "start": 126.518,
      "end": 128.638,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "那应该怎么读？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 9,
      "start": 128.988,
      "end": 141.512,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "读成一个新住户学习街区规则的故事。叙述者刚搬来，所以他看到 Percy 时觉得陌生、突然、不可思议。邻居却很淡定，因为"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "everybody knows him"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 10,
      "start": 141.861,
      "end": 147.31,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "像新同学刚进班，发现大家都知道某个小传统，只有他不知道？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 11,
      "start": 147.659,
      "end": 166.219,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "对，就是这个感觉。你刚进一个班，大家知道每周五要带阅读记录，知道校门口哪位保安叔叔总会提醒排队，知道小卖部门口有个常来的熟人。新人看见会问：“这是谁？为什么大家都不惊讶？”老成员就会说：“哦，大家都认识他。”"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 12,
      "start": 166.569,
      "end": 170.496,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "但是现实里有人敲门，小朋友不能自己开门。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 13,
      "start": 170.846,
      "end": 191.046,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "必须说清楚：今天在中国的高层小区、学校、家里，如果陌生人敲门，小朋友不应该独自开门，也不要自己处理。应该叫爸爸妈妈、门卫、老师或邻居。课文讲的是老式英国街屋的故事场景，不是现代安全建议。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 14,
      "start": 191.396,
      "end": 195.937,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "题目"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Percy Buttons"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "就是那个人的名字？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 15,
      "start": 196.287,
      "end": 220.639,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "对，中文可以说珀西·巴顿斯。故事结尾才报出名字，就像邻居递给叙述者一张“本地说明书”。还有一个特别容易错的短语："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "calls at"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。这里不是打电话，意思是“拜访、到某个地方停一下”。所以"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He calls at every house"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "不是“他给每家打电话”，而是“他拜访每一家”。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 16,
      "start": 220.989,
      "end": 228.862,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "那"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "once a month"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "和"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "always asks"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "就说明这不是偶然。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 17,
      "start": 229.212,
      "end": 245.232,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "没错。昨天发生的是一次事件；邻居告诉我们的，是一个长期习惯。笑点就在这里：我以为遇到了一件奇怪的一次性事件，结果整条街都知道，这是每个月都会来的固定惯例。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 18,
      "start": 245.582,
      "end": 248.822,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I have just moved to a house in Bridge Street."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 19,
      "start": 249.172,
      "end": 252.148,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Yesterday a beggar knocked at my door."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 20,
      "start": 252.498,
      "end": 255.666,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He asked me for a meal and a glass of beer."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 21,
      "start": 256.015,
      "end": 260.431,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "In return for this, the beggar stood on his head and sang songs."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 22,
      "start": 260.781,
      "end": 262.893,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I gave him a meal."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 23,
      "start": 263.243,
      "end": 266.051,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He ate the food and drank the beer."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 24,
      "start": 266.401,
      "end": 270.169,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Then he put a piece of cheese in his pocket and went away."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 25,
      "start": 270.519,
      "end": 273.183,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Later a neighbour told me about him."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 26,
      "start": 273.533,
      "end": 275.549,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Everybody knows him."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 27,
      "start": 275.899,
      "end": 278.467,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "His name is Percy Buttons."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 28,
      "start": 278.817,
      "end": 284.481,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He calls at every house in the street once a month and always asks for a meal and a glass of beer."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 29,
      "start": 284.83,
      "end": 287.326,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "beggar"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第一个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "beggar"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 30,
      "start": 287.676,
      "end": 289.26,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "beggar"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "beggar"
        },
        {
