        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 31,
      "start": 289.61,
      "end": 303.386,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "beggar"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "beggar"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“乞讨者、乞丐”。这个词说的是处境，不是笑点。读故事时要保持尊重：课文的幽默来自街区惯例和新人信息差，不来自嘲笑一个穷人。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 32,
      "start": 303.736,
      "end": 307.096,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "return"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二个重点短语："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "in return for"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 33,
      "start": 307.446,
      "end": 309.534,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "return"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "in return for"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 34,
      "start": 309.884,
      "end": 325.971,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "return"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "in return for"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "的意思是“作为回报、作为交换”。Percy 请求一顿饭和一杯啤酒；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "in return for this"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，他倒立唱歌。你可以把它理解成：我得到这个，所以我用那个来回报。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 35,
      "start": 326.321,
      "end": 330.049,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "call"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三个重点短语："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "call at"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 36,
      "start": 330.399,
      "end": 332.055,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "call"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "call at"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 37,
      "start": 332.405,
      "end": 347.524,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "call"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这里一定不要按手机来理解。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "call at"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "不是“打电话”，而是“拜访、顺路到某个地方停一下”。课文里"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He calls at every house"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "的意思是：他会拜访街上的每一户人家。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 38,
      "start": 347.874,
      "end": 388.434,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的语法，不背成表格，放进故事逻辑里看。第一句"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I have just moved"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，重点是“我现在是刚搬来的新人”，所以我不知道本地情况。后面"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Yesterday a beggar knocked"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "、"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "asked"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "、"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "stood"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "、"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "sang"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，是在讲昨天发生的一串动作。最后"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "He calls at every house once a month and always asks"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，就变成规律了：他每个月都会来，而且总是提出同样的请求。三个时间层次合起来，就是这篇故事的笑点：新情况、昨天的事件、长期的惯例。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 39,
      "start": 388.784,
      "end": 407.944,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "好，把这个“新搬来的人还不知道本地惯例”的感觉，放进现代安全场景。下面有三个空：刚搬来、有人敲门、邻居解释。你从 word bank 里选短语补上。记住，现实里遇到陌生人敲门，小朋友要先找大人。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 40,
      "start": 408.293,
      "end": 423.117,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "老师刚搬家时，也不认识小区门口的熟人。有一次有人敲门，我先叫家里大人去看，后来邻居说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Everybody knows him."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "原来那是经常来帮大家收旧纸箱的叔叔。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
